ation. Here's what you asked for:\n\n## Function Signature\n\n```typescript\nasync insertUserTransaction(params: InsertUserTransactionParams): Promise<void>\n```\n\nThe function is located at lines 533-546 in the file.\n\n## Type Definitions\n\n**`UserTransactionEvent`** (line 104):\n```typescript\nexport type UserTransactionEvent = \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\";\n```\n\n**`InsertUserTransactionParams`** (lines 117-124):\n```typescript\nexport interface InsertUserTransactionParams {\n  wallet: string;\n  game: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  event: UserTransactionEvent;\n  amountLamports: number;\n  txSig?: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\nThe function inserts a row into the `user_transactions` table with the following SQL columns:\n- `wallet`\n- `game`\n- `match_id` (from camelCase `matchId`)\n- `event`\n- `amount_lamports` (from camelCase `amountLamports`)\n- `tx_sig` (from camelCase `txSig`, optional, defaults to null)\n\nThe query uses `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` for idempotency (lines 544), meaning duplicate inserts are silently ignored."}],"totalDurationMs":6642,"totalTokens":39272,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9546,"cache_read_input_tokens":29401,"output_tokens":320,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9546},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
