{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PFNMRbpbgUyxXZhws5Ty3J","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the complete file contents for `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`:\n\n## Key Sections You Asked About\n\n### settleMatch() function (lines 143–327) — Coinflip settlement\n\nThe payout computation happens at **lines 203–205**:\n```typescript\nconst pool = entryAmount * 2n;\nconst feeAmount = Number((pool * 300n) / 10_000n);\nconst payoutAmount = Number(pool) - feeAmount;\n```\n\nThis calculates:\n- **pool**: both players' amounts combined (entryAmount × 2)\n- **feeAmount**: 3% of the pool (300 bps / 10,000)\n- **payoutAmount**: pool minus fees (what the winner receives)\n\nThe **settle_confirmed event** is logged at **lines 293–302**:\n```typescript\nawait db.insertOperatorEvent(pda, \"settle_confirmed\", {\n  txSignature,\n  resultSide,\n  winner: winner.toBase58(),\n  entropy: entropy.toString(\"hex\"),\n  payoutAmount,\n  feeAmount,\n  entries: coinflipEntries,\n});\n```\n\nThis records the settlement details including:\n- Transaction signature and result\n- Winner's address (Solana pubkey)\n- Payout and fee amounts\n- Entry records for both players\n\n### settleLordRound() function (lines 329–520)\n\nSimilar structure to Coinflip, but handles weighted entries (jackpot mechanics):\n\n**Payout computation at lines 392–394**:\n```typescript\nconst feeAmount = Number((roundData.totalAmountLamports * 300n) / 10_000n);\nconst payoutAmount = Number(roundData.totalAmountLamports) - feeAmount;\nconst rentRefund = roundAccountInfo.lamports - Number(roundData.totalAmountLamports);\n```\n\n**Winner selection at lines 396–409**:\nThe winning offset is derived from the result hash (line 397):\n```typescript\nconst winningOffset = raw % roundData.totalAmountLamports;\n```\n\nThen iterates through entries cumulatively to find which entry index owns that offset (lines 399–409). This implements the weighted lottery where entry size determines probability.\n\n**settle_confirmed event at lines 483–495** includes:\n- Winner address and entry index\n- Winning offset and total pool amount\n- Entry list (all participating players)\n- Rent refund amount (unique to Lord since accounts are closed)\n\nBoth functions follow the same pattern: fetch DB record → retrieve on-chain state → compute result deterministically → build + sign transaction → confirm → log event."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af1ca8100ffb07578 (use SendMessage with to: 'af1ca8100ffb07578' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 43103\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 10005</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab81b221-6f6d-4c3b-b1b4-ab27917ca48e","uuid":"14968a23-7dbe-41df-b038-3ade3538e2da","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:44:03.728Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the full file at /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts and report its contents back to me. I need to see the complete file to understand the settleMatch() function, especially around line 286 where settle_confirmed event happens and the payout computation. Also show the settleLordRound function around line 466.","agentId":"af1ca8100ffb07578","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the complete file contents for `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`:\n\n## Key Sections You Asked About\n\n### settleMatch() function (lines 143–327) — Coinflip settlement\n\nThe payout computation happens at **lines 203–205**:\n```typescript\nconst pool = entryAmount * 2n;\nconst feeAmount = Number((pool * 300n) / 10_000n);\nconst payoutAmount = Number(pool) - feeAmount;\n```\n\nThis calculates:\n- **pool**: both players' amounts combined (entryAmount × 2)\n- **feeAmount**: 3% of the pool (300 bps / 10,000)\n- **payoutAmount**: pool minus fees (what the winner receives)\n\nThe **settle_confirmed event** is logged at **lines 293–302**:\n```typescript\nawait db.insertOperatorEvent(pda, \"settle_confirmed\", {\n  txSignature,\n  resultSide,\n  winner: winner.toBase58(),\n  entropy: entropy.toString(\"hex\"),\n  payoutAmount,\n  feeAmount,\n  entries: coinflipEntries,\n});\n```\n\nThis records the settlement details including:\n- Transaction signature and result\n- Winner's address (Solana pubkey)\n- Payout and fee amounts\n- Entry records for both players\n\n### settleLordRound() function (lines 329–520)\n\nSimilar structure to Coinflip, but handles weighted entries (jackpot mechanics):\n\n**Payout computation at lines 392–394**:\n```typescript\nconst feeAmount = Number((roundData.totalAmountLamports * 300n) / 10_000n);\nconst payoutAmount = Number(roundData.totalAmountLamports) - feeAmount;\nconst rentRefund = roundAccountInfo.lamports - Number(roundData.totalAmountLamports);\n```\n\n**Winner selection at lines 396–409**:\nThe winning offset is derived from the result hash (line 397):\n```typescript\nconst winningOffset = raw % roundData.totalAmountLamports;\n```\n\nThen iterates through entries cumulatively to find which entry index owns that offset (lines 399–409). This implements the weighted lottery where entry size determines probability.\n\n**settle_confirmed event at lines 483–495** includes:\n- Winner address and entry index\n- Winning offset and total pool amount\n- Entry list (all participating players)\n- Rent refund amount (unique to Lord since accounts are closed)\n\nBoth functions follow the same pattern: fetch DB record → retrieve on-chain state → compute result deterministically → build + sign transaction → confirm → log event."}],"totalDurationMs":10005,"totalTokens":43103,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13023,"cache_read_input_tokens":29429,"output_tokens":646,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"epheme