{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Eavdq9j3yCp7CbMeZjZ36d","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete `pda-watcher.ts` file:\n\n## File Contents Summary\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/pda-watcher.ts`\n\nThe file is a WebSocket-based PDA (Program Derived Account) watcher that monitors match and round accounts for phase changes to enable instant settlement detection instead of relying on poll-based cycles.\n\n### Key Sections\n\n**Lines 1-19**: Module documentation and imports\n- Explains the dramatic latency reduction: ~13s (stale poll) → ~1-3s (WebSocket + settlement)\n- Imports Connection, PublicKey from Solana web3.js and decoders from account-decoder.ts\n\n**Lines 22-40**: Type definitions\n- `PdaWatcherDeps`: Connection, serverKey, and onJoinDetected callback\n- `PdaWatcher` interface: watch(), unwatch(), stopAll() methods, and size property\n\n**Lines 46-48**: Constants\n- `COINFLIP_MATCH_SIZE`: Size of coinflip match account\n- `PHASE_LOCKED = 1`: Phase value indicating lock\n- `LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE = 1`: Phase value for active lord round\n\n**Lines 54-99**: `watch()` function\n- Registers a PDA for WebSocket subscription\n- Calls `connection.onAccountChange()` with callback\n- Handles account closure (lamports === 0)\n- Routes to game-specific handler based on account size (Coinflip vs. Lord)\n\n**Lines 101-124**: `handleCoinflipChange()` function — **The critical lock detection logic around line 113**\n```typescript\n// Line 110: Only care about our server's matches that are now locked\nif (match.phase !== PHASE_LOCKED || !match.server.equals(serverKey)) return;\nif (match.targetSlot <= 0n) return;\n\n// Line 113: Logs the lock detection\nlogger.info(\"[pda-watcher] coinflip phase changed to locked\", {\n  pda: pda.slice(0, 12),\n  targetSlot: match.targetSlot.toString(),\n});\n\n// Line 118: Triggers onJoinDetected callback\nonJoinDetected(pda, match.targetSlot).catch((err) => { ... });\n```\n\n**Lines 126-149**: `handleLordChange()` function\n- Similar logic for Lord of RNGs rounds\n- Checks `round.phase === LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE`\n- Validates `targetEntropySlot > 0`\n- Triggers `onJoinDetected` callback\n\n**Lines 151-181**: Factory return with `unwatch()`, `stopAll()`, and size getter\n\nThe lock detection at line 110 is the gate: it only processes matches where `phase === 1` (PHASE_LOCKED) and the server public key matches, ensuring only the creating server settles its own matches."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a942e305b95eaece5 (use SendMessage with to: 'a942e305b95eaece5' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 34567\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 12667</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab81b221-6f6d-4c3b-b1b4-ab27917ca48e","uuid":"27347941-6d81-4219-a12c-5829c9b3ac49","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:44:04.439Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the full file at /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/pda-watcher.ts and report its contents back to me. I need to see the complete file to understand the handleCoinflipChange function, especially around line 113 where lock detection happens.","agentId":"a942e305b95eaece5","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete `pda-watcher.ts` file:\n\n## File Contents Summary\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/pda-watcher.ts`\n\nThe file is a WebSocket-based PDA (Program Derived Account) watcher that monitors match and round accounts for phase changes to enable instant settlement detection instead of relying on poll-based cycles.\n\n### Key Sections\n\n**Lines 1-19**: Module documentation and imports\n- Explains the dramatic latency reduction: ~13s (stale poll) → ~1-3s (WebSocket + settlement)\n- Imports Connection, PublicKey from Solana web3.js and decoders from account-decoder.ts\n\n**Lines 22-40**: Type definitions\n- `PdaWatcherDeps`: Connection, serverKey, and onJoinDetected callback\n- `PdaWatcher` interface: watch(), unwatch(), stopAll() methods, and size property\n\n**Lines 46-48**: Constants\n- `COINFLIP_MATCH_SIZE`: Size of coinflip match account\n- `PHASE_LOCKED = 1`: Phase value indicating lock\n- `LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE = 1`: Phase value for active lord round\n\n**Lines 54-99**: `watch()` function\n- Registers a PDA for WebSocket subscription\n- Calls `connection.onAccountChange()` with callback\n- Handles account closure (lamports === 0)\n- Routes to game-specific handler based on account size (Coinflip vs. Lord)\n\n**Lines 101-124**: `handleCoinflipChange()` function — **The critical lock detection logic around line 113**\n```typescript\n// Line 110: Only care about our server's matches that are now locked\nif (match.phase !== PHASE_LOCKED || !match.server.equals(serverKey)) return;\nif (match.targetSlot <= 0n) return;\n\n// Line 113: Logs the lock detection\nlogger.info(\"[pda-watcher] coinflip phase changed to locked\", {\n  pda: pda.slice(0, 12),\n  targetSlot: match.targetSlot.toString(),\n});\n\n// Line 118: Triggers onJoinDetected callback\nonJoinDetected(pda, match.targetSlot).catch((err) => { ... });\n```\n\n**Lines 126-149**: `handleLordChange()` function\n- Similar logic for Lord of RNGs rounds\n- Checks `round.phase === LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE`\n- Validates `targetEntropySlot > 0`\n- Triggers `onJoinDetected` callback\n\n**Lines 151-181**: Factory return with `unwatch()`, `stopAll()`, and size getter\n\nThe lock detection at line 110 is the gate: it only processes matches where `phase === 1` (PHASE_LOCKED) and the server public key matches, ensuring only the creating server settles its own matches."}],"totalDurationMs":12667,"totalTokens":34567,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9067,"cache_read_input_tokens":24785,"output_tokens":710,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard",